# Task

Define the core Signature trait that replaces MetaSignature for typed API.

## File
`crates/dspy-rs/src/core/signature.rs`

## Trait Definition

```rust
/// Typed signature trait - implemented by #[derive(Signature)] macro.
/// 
/// Unlike MetaSignature which uses runtime Value, this provides compile-time
/// type safety through associated types.
pub trait Signature: Send + Sync + 'static {
    /// Input struct type (e.g., QAInput)
    /// Must implement BamlType for schema generation
    type Input: baml_bridge::BamlType + Send + Sync;

    /// Output-only struct type (e.g., __QAOutput)
    /// Hidden from users, used for parsing
    type Output: baml_bridge::BamlType + Send + Sync;

    /// Instruction extracted from doc comment
    fn instruction() -> &'static str;

    /// Input field metadata for prompt formatting
    fn input_fields() -> &'static [FieldSpec];

    /// Output field metadata for parsing and schema
    fn output_fields() -> &'static [FieldSpec];

    /// Pre-computed output schema for LLM prompts
    /// Static lifetime because computed once at startup
    fn output_format_content() -> &'static OutputFormatContent;

    /// Construct full signature struct from input + parsed output
    /// Called after successful parsing
    fn from_parts(input: Self::Input, output: Self::Output) -> Self;

    /// Decompose into input and output parts
    /// Used for demo formatting
    fn into_parts(self) -> (Self::Input, Self::Output);
}
```

## Design Notes

### Why Associated Types?
- Enables `Predict<S: Signature>` - generic over signature
- Compile-time type checking of inputs/outputs
- No trait object indirection for hot path

### Why from_parts/into_parts?
- `from_parts`: After parsing `__QAOutput`, construct the full `QA` struct
- `into_parts`: For demos, split `QA` into input fields (for user message) and output fields (for assistant message)

### Why output_format_content() -> &'static?
- Schema is computed once per type (OnceLock in generated code)
- Avoid recomputing on every call
- Safe because OutputFormatContent is immutable

## Relationship to MetaSignature

MetaSignature (legacy):
- `fn demos(&self)` - runtime demo storage
- `fn input_fields(&self) -> Value` - JSON schema blob
- `fn update_instruction(&mut self)` - mutable

Signature (new):
- No demo storage (Predict<S> holds demos)
- Static field metadata (FieldSpec arrays)
- Immutable (all methods are associated functions)

